---
id: org.dxos.plugin.studio
name: StudioPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A studio for **creative artifacts** in `DXOS` Composer. An `Artifact` is a
media-agnostic unit of creative work — a prompt plus the outputs generated (or
uploaded) from it — spanning images, video, and future media. The plugin owns
the cross-cutting ontology and the generic authoring UI; concrete media
(rendering) and providers (generation) plug in via capabilities and surfaces.

`plugin-studio` is the evolution of `plugin-studio` (renamed): it generalizes
`ImageArtifact` → `Artifact`, `Image` → `Variant`, and folds the gallery/board
layouts onto the existing `Collection` / `Board` types.

## Design tenets

- **One extensible `Artifact` type**, discriminated by an open-string `kind`
  (`'image' | 'video' | …`). No per-medium ECHO types; new media add *behavior*
  (a renderer + a provider), never columns.
- **Two output relationships**: `variants` (interchangeable alternatives of the
  primary output — the user picks a `cover`) vs. `derived` (downstream products
  such as a video transcript/summary or an image caption).
- **Rendering is a Surface, keyed by `contentType`.** Studio ships defaults
  (`image/*` → `<img>`, `video/*` → `<video>`); any plugin overrides via a
  higher-priority (`Position.first`) surface. Defaults may later graduate into
  `plugin-studio` / `plugin-video`.
- **Generation is kind-specific.** A provider contributes a `GenerationService`
  for a `kind` with its own **`requestSchema`** (Effect Schema) describing that
  medium's request config; studio renders the request form from the schema
  (generic `Form`) or a provider-supplied custom UI (a Surface).
- **Layout reuses existing types**: a masonry gallery is a `Collection<Artifact>`;
  a spatial lightbox is a `Board<Artifact>`. Layout is a *view*, not a schema.
- **Credentialed access via Connectors** (unchanged): providers store an
  `AccessToken`; the generate op resolves it via `CredentialsService`.

## Scope of this milestone

| Package             | Change |
| ------------------- | ------ |
| `plugin-studio`     | Rename of `plugin-studio`. New `Artifact`/`Variant`/`Generation` ontology, `GenerationService` contract (per-`kind`, with `requestSchema`), generic `ArtifactArticle` + default variant renderers + schema-driven generate form, `Collection`/`Board` gallery/lightbox surfaces, media-agnostic `generate` op. Deletes `ImageArtifact`/`Image`/`Gallery`. |
| `plugin-ideogram`   | Re-registers as the `kind:'image'` `GenerationService`; contributes its `requestSchema` (prompt/aspectRatio/model/style/seed/count). Imports `@dxos/plugin-studio/types`. |
| `plugin-video`      | **Untouched this milestone.** Studio ships a default `video/*` renderer to prove the pattern; subsuming `Video` → `Artifact{kind:'video'}` (transcript/summary as `derived`) is a follow-up. |

> **Types graduation**: `Artifact`/`Variant`/`Generation` live in
> `plugin-studio/types` now (siblings import `@dxos/plugin-studio/types`); they
> are generic enough to graduate to `@dxos/types` later via a namespace
> re-export without touching call sites.

